data.title: Cupboard
data.description: Some cupboards are built into a wall, like a closet, while others are freestanding cabinets. A cupboard usually has doors that open and shelves inside, for storage. The very earliest cupboards, in the 14th century, were exactly what the word describes: a board or table used for putting cups or dishes on. Over the following two hundred years, cupboard came to mean an enclosed cabinet for the same purpose.

data.title: Table
data.description: This 2-tiered coffee table completes your living room with a modern look and extra storage. Its made with a steel circular openwork frame in a smooth black tone.The top surface is crafted from engineered wood and features a faux white marble finish – all the glamor of a marble, without the weight.We love that the lower shelf of this coffee table is made from transparent glass, so its great for storing books and tech without taking up too much visual space.
